<div id="descriptionContainer">
  
      <div id="description" class="readable stacked" style="right:0">
        
<span id="freeTextContainer9384906621233954952">When it was published in 1995, Mary Karr&apos;s <i>The Liars Club</i> took the world by storm and raised the art of the memoir to an entirely new level, as well as bringing about a dramatic revival of the form. Karr&apos;s comic childhood in an east Texas oil town brings us characters as darkly hilarious as any of J. D. Salinger&apos;s—a hard-drinking daddy, a sister who can talk down the sheri</span>
  <span id="freeText9384906621233954952" style="display:none">When it was published in 1995, Mary Karr's <i>The Liars Club</i> took the world by storm and raised the art of the memoir to an entirely new level, as well as bringing about a dramatic revival of the form. Karr's comic childhood in an east Texas oil town brings us characters as darkly hilarious as any of J. D. Salinger's—a hard-drinking daddy, a sister who can talk down the sheriff at twelve, and an oft-married mother whose accumulated secrets threaten to destroy them all. Now with a new introduction that discusses her memoir's impact on her family, this unsentimental and profoundly moving account of an apocalyptic childhood is as "funny, lively, and un-put-downable" (<i>USA Today</i>) today as it ever was.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9384906621233954952" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

