<div id="review_82038187" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/82038187" />
    <a title="Linden" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2320615-linden"><img alt="Linden" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1262105925p2/2320615.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/82038187?book_show_action=true">Dec 25, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Linden" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Linden" href="/user/show/2320615-linden">Linden</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer82038187" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5543630778732085671">This book has compelling images and moves along quickly. After reading about half of it, though, I realized that I was really irritated by the voice. She doesn&apos;t have much grace, and the wisdom she professes to have doesn&apos;t ring true. I started to feel very manipulated. She has plenty of painful memories, and she writes about them with a lot of sensory detail. But I didn&apos;t come away with a sense that she had made peace with her past, nor that she had a greater understanding of what life was all </span>
  <span id="freeText5543630778732085671" style="display:none">This book has compelling images and moves along quickly. After reading about half of it, though, I realized that I was really irritated by the voice. She doesn't have much grace, and the wisdom she professes to have doesn't ring true. I started to feel very manipulated. She has plenty of painful memories, and she writes about them with a lot of sensory detail. But I didn't come away with a sense that she had made peace with her past, nor that she had a greater understanding of what life was all about. It was more like "I have had this horrible stuff happen, look at me, look at me!" <br /><br />Then I heard her talk and realized that she is very, very angry and needs a lot of attention. She opened a poetry reading in Berkeley by cursing at the introducer and saying he was worthless. This totally sealed my opinion of her, which is that she hasn't gotten to a higher level of grace or wisdom but is selling her story because it sells. Period.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5543630778732085671" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


