<div id="review_2607241193" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2607241193" />
    <a title="Mary Blye Kramer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15925729-mary-blye-kramer"><img alt="Mary Blye Kramer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607792408p2/15925729.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2607241193?book_show_action=true">Dec 09, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mary Blye Kramer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mary Blye Kramer" href="/user/show/15925729-mary-blye-kramer">Mary Blye Kramer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2607241193" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10988410683536508215">This was my second reading of this book; the first reading was nearly 19 years ago. I wrote in the inside cover, as I always do, the date and what I thought about the book, both times. Excellent writer, captivating and heartbreaking memoir. This time through I went more slowly and picked up on Karr’s humor and vivid detail, especially since I’m simultaneously reading her book on writing memoirs and writing a third one myself. Karr’s writing and her story is mesmerizing and I love her voice. <br/><br/>Two </span>
  <span id="freeText10988410683536508215" style="display:none">This was my second reading of this book; the first reading was nearly 19 years ago. I wrote in the inside cover, as I always do, the date and what I thought about the book, both times. Excellent writer, captivating and heartbreaking memoir. This time through I went more slowly and picked up on Karr’s humor and vivid detail, especially since I’m simultaneously reading her book on writing memoirs and writing a third one myself. Karr’s writing and her story is mesmerizing and I love her voice. <br /><br />Two hesitations, though. One, her second rape, I could have done with less detail. I’m sure it was horrible for her to write, but really, I didn’t need that picture in my head. <br /><br />Two, this time around she lost my credibility with the story of dinner with her mom at the end of the book when she explains away all of her mom’s horrible behavior. I know people who do wicked things have probably had a background that explains their behavior, but please don’t justify it to me. She stands with a knife about to kill her kids and she abandons two others and that explains her gross negligence and horrific mothering of Mary and her sister? Uh uh.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10988410683536508215" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


